<title>INDIA: India RBI nod must for buying in HDFC, Infosys.</title>
<headline>India RBI nod must for buying in HDFC, Infosys.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) said on Monday that fresh purchases by foreign institutional investors (FIIs) in two top shares would need its prior approval.</p>
<p>Aggregate net purchases in Housing Development Finance Corp Ltd (HDFC) and Infosys Technologies Ltd by foreign portfolio investors have reached a watch-list limit of 26 percent, the RBI said in a statement.</p>
<p>The ceiling on FII holdings in both the stocks is 30 percent.</p>
<p>--Bombay equities desk +91-22-265-9000</p>
